{
    return 1.0 / x;
}The reciprocal of some numberxis defined as1/x, and a number multiplied by its reciprocal equals 1.However, what happens if the user calls this function asreciprocal(0.0)? We get adivide by zeroerror and a program crash, so clearly we should protect against this case. But this function must return a double value, so what value should we return? It turns out that this function will never produce0.0as a legitimate result, so we can return0.0to indicate an error case.// The reciprocal of x is 1/x, returns 0.0 if x=0
